<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-01-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-01-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="426" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d426">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 4001/7.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Governor of Jamaica</gloss>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Jamaica</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-01-20"><hi rend="italic">January 20,
                                1907</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Jamaica profoundly grateful to your excellency for expression of sympathy
                            and for the very practical aid so kindly given by Admiral Davis and the
                            entire particular service squadron of the United States Navy.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Governor.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>